commits.author: Dawid Weiss
commits.sourceNew:
/** Expert: returns the sequential sub readers that this * reader is logically composed of. For example, * IndexSearcher uses this API to drive searching by one * sub reader at a time. If this reader is not composed * of sequential child readers, it should return null. * If this method returns an empty array, that means this * reader is a null reader (for example a MultiReader * that has no sub readers). *

* NOTE: You should not try using sub-readers returned by * this method to make any changes (setNorm, deleteDocument, * etc.). While this might succeed for one composite reader * (like MultiReader), it will most likely lead to index * corruption for other readers (like DirectoryReader obtained * through {@link #open}. Use the parent reader directly. */ public IndexReader[] getSequentialSubReaders() { return null; }
